\f0\fs24 \cf0 Scaled electrochemical reduction of CO2 to CO in membrane-electrode assembly\
\

\f1\b Starting from 5cm2 MEA electrolyzer
\f0\b0 :cell configuration as AgNPs (50nm, 0.3-0.6 mg/cm2) || AEM || IrO2-TiPt. The flow-field channels of both anode and cathode are single-serpentine flow-field.\

\f1\b Operation
\f0\b0 : 4ml/min 0.1M KHCO3, 0.5M CH3COOH acid humidified 20ml/min CO2 (4ml/min/cm2) at 100mA/cm2 (500mA)\
*Anode flow pattern: Liquid In from bottom to top.\
*Cathode flow pattern: Gas In from top to bottom.\
* 40ml of CH3COOH solution was poured in 100mL Duran bottle\
* 2L of 0.1M KHCO3 was used and refreshed every 4days of continuous operation as the pH drops from 8.5 to ~7.1-7.3.\
*During the operation, the CO2 outlet remains 14.5-15.5 ml/min as some of carbonate anion has crossed over from cathode to anode which then reoxidizes to CO2 at the anode compartment (considered as CO2 loss).\
* FE(CO): ~90-95%, FE(H2):~1-5%, FE(formate) = 100- FE(CO) + FE(H2)\
*Cell voltage or potential: 3.3 - 3.5V at 100mA/cm2\
\

\f1\b 100cm2 MEA electrolyzer operation based on 5cm2 MEA device
\f0\b0 : Same cell configuration. The flow-field channels of anode and cathode are parallel and single-serpentine, respectively.\
