\f0\b0 : 100-150ml/min 0.1M KHCO3, 0.05M CH3COOH acid humidified 200ml/min CO2 (2ml/min/cm2) at 100mA/cm2 (10A)\
*Anode flow pattern: Liquid In from bottom to top.\
*Cathode flow pattern: Gas In from top to bottom.\
* 500ml of CH3COOH solution was poured in 700mL humidifier bottle\
* 10L of 0.1M KHCO3 was used as the electrolyte\
*During the operation, the CO2 outlet remains 120-125 ml/min as some of carbonate anion has crossed over from cathode to anode which then reoxidizes to CO2 at the anode compartment (considered as CO2 loss).\
* FE(CO): ~90-95%, FE(H2):~1-5%, FE(formate) = 100- FE(CO) + FE(H2)\
*Cell voltage or potential: 3.3 - 3.5V at 100mA/cm2\
